  "prompt": "When is it likely that the proposed extended maternity leave from 12 to 26 weeks will be implemented for private sectors in India?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the Indian government had already extended maternity leave from 12 weeks to 26 weeks under the Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, 2017. This applies to establishments with 10 or more employees in the organized sector, including private sectors. The amendment came into effect on April 1, 2017.\n\nHowever, the implementation and awareness of this extended maternity leave can vary across different sectors and organizations. If you are referring to a new or different proposal for extended maternity leave, I would need more specific information to provide an accurate answer. \n\nFor the most current information or any new proposals, it would be best to check recent government announcements or consult legal resources specific to labor laws in India.",
